{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3071 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3071 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C3071","pos":[597,617]},{"content":"operator 'operator' can only be applied to an instance of a ref class or a value-type","pos":[618,703]},{"content":"A CLR operator cannot be used on a native type.","pos":[710,757]},{"content":"The operator can be used on a ref class or a ref struct (a value type) but not a native type such as int or an alias for a native type such as System::Int32.","pos":[758,915]},{"content":"These types can't be boxed from C++ code in a way that refers to the native variable, so the operator cannot be used.","pos":[916,1033]},{"pos":[1040,1167],"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Tracking Reference Operator<ept id=\"p1\">](../../windows/tracking-reference-operator-cpp-component-extensions.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information, see [Tracking Reference Operator](../../windows/tracking-reference-operator-cpp-component-extensions.md)."},{"content":"Example","pos":[1176,1183]},{"content":"The following sample generates C3071.","pos":[1187,1224]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3071 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3071\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3071\"\nms.assetid: 69879e66-a60e-4058-9bbd-d5c5e2d8ee37\ncaps.latest.revision: 7\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3071\noperator 'operator' can only be applied to an instance of a ref class or a value-type  \n  \n A CLR operator cannot be used on a native type. The operator can be used on a ref class or a ref struct (a value type) but not a native type such as int or an alias for a native type such as System::Int32. These types can't be boxed from C++ code in a way that refers to the native variable, so the operator cannot be used.  \n  \n For more information, see [Tracking Reference Operator](../../windows/tracking-reference-operator-cpp-component-extensions.md).  \n  \n## Example  \n The following sample generates C3071.  \n  \n```  \n// C3071.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr  \nclass N {};  \nref struct R {};  \n  \nint main() {  \n   N n;  \n   %n;   // C3071  \n  \n   R r;  \n   R ^ r2 = %r;   // OK  \n}  \n```"}